linear-gradient(120deg, transparent 0%, transparent 50%, white 50%);
We have to set an angle degree to gvet the animation work.
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/linear-gradient()


background-size: 220%; The background-size CSS property sets the size 
of the element's background image. The image can be left to its natural size,
stretched, or constrained to fit the available space.

background-position: 100%; The background-position property sets the 
starting position of a background image.

transition: all .4s; CSS transitions allows you to change property values 
smoothly, over a given duration.
https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_transitions.asp



transform: translateX(1rem); The transform property applies a 2D or 3D 
transformation to an element. This property allows you to rotate, scale, 
move, skew, etc., elements.
https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css3_pr_transform.asp


background-image: radial-gradient(rgb(255, 251, 15), darkgreen);
To create a radial gradient you must also define at least two color stops.
background-image: radial-gradient(shape size at position, start-color, ..., last-color);
By default, shape is ellipse, size is farthest-corner, and position is center.
https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_gradients_radial.asp


General Sibling Selector (~)
The general sibling selector selects all elements that are siblings of a specified element.
https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_combinators.asp

